# jemdoc: 
= Yeshwanth Cherapanamjeri

~~~
{}{img_left}{images/profile.jpg}{Picture}{280}{300}{}
*Yeshwanth Cherapanamjeri* \n
/Postdoc/ \n
[https://www.csail.mit.edu/ CSAIL] \n
[https://www.mit.edu/ MIT] \n
\n \n
I am a postdoc at MIT where I am mentored by [http://people.csail.mit.edu/costis/ Costis Daskalakis]. I obtained my Ph.D at UC Berkeley where I was fortunate to be advised by [https://www.stat.berkeley.edu/~bartlett/ Peter Bartlett]. I'm broadly interested in algorithmic and statistical issues arising in machine learning. Before this, I'd spent two wonderful years as a research fellow in the Machine Learning & Optimization group at Microsoft Research, India, where I was fortunate to work with [https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/prajain/ Prateek Jain], [https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/praneeth/ Praneeth Netrapalli] and Nagarajan Natarajan on designing provable algorithms for non-convex optimization. Previously, I received a B. Tech in Computer Science from IIT Bombay where I worked on Entity Linking and Disambiguation with [https://www.cse.iitb.ac.in/~ganesh/ Prof. Ganesh Ramakrishnan] and [https://www.cse.iitb.ac.in/~soumen/ Prof. Soumen Chakrabarti] for my undergraduate thesis.
\n \n
You can find a link to my resume [docs/resume.pdf here].

~~~

